HEADWORD: Nine-killer
<hw>Nine"-kill`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called
because it is believed to kill and impale on thorns nine birds, etc., in
succession.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The northern butcher
bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

